Titolo: BlazBlue: Continuum Shift

Anno: 2009

Descrizione: BlazBlue: Continuum Shift is a 2009 fighting game developed by Arc System Works as an official sequel to BlazBlue: Calamity Trigger. As with the previous game, the game first came to arcades before both the Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3 versions as the game was currently released for the Taito Type X2 arcade system board, with a 16:9 ratio and 768p resolution.
Revisions entitled BlazBlue: Continuum Shift II and BlazBlue: Continuum Shift Extend were released in arcades in 2010â€“2011. They were later ported to the PlayStation 3, PlayStation Portable, Nintendo 3DS, and Windows.